description.narrative: UNICEF continues to provide technical leadership on Children and Armed Conflict and Mine Action in Myanmar. UNICEF, as co-chair of the Country Task Force on Monitoring and Reporting and co-lead the Mine Risk Working Group organized high-level advocacy with Government, donors and key international actors to advance Children and Armed Conflict agenda. UNICEF's continuous engagement with all listed parties led to continued progress on the Joint Action Plan with Tatmadaw to end under-age recruitment and very close to signing of Joint Commitment with two listed non-state actors (NSAs). | Status:On-track | As-of Date:28/07/2020
